      { q: 'Light of wavelength 450 nm falls on a diffraction grating with 300 lines/mm. How many complete orders are visible?', options: ['3', '5', '7', '9'], answer: 'C', explanation: 'd = 1/(300×10³) = 3.33×10⁻⁶ m; n_max = d/λ = 3.33×10⁻⁶/450×10⁻⁹ = 7.4; so 7 complete orders visible.' }
